OL,3,CAntakya earthquake: A city of rubble
OL,4,Cand grief remains one year on
OL,6,FAntakya was the worst hit. 20,000 died
OL,7,Fhere, hundreds of thousands now live
OL,8,Fin tiny prefabricated containers.
OL,10,FAt least in the containers they do not
OL,11,Fhave the fear their homes will
OL,12,Fcollapse upon them once more.
OL,14,FThose they loved and lost, their homes
OL,15,Fand their city are now memories. Some
OL,16,Fhave still not recovered the bodies of
OL,17,Ftheir dead.
OL,19,FEven those who knew the ancient city
OL,20,Fwell would struggle to navigate it now.
